\begin{align*}
a + b + c &= 0 \\
ab + bc + ca &= p \\
abc &= -q \end{align*>
\begin{align*}
(a + b + c)^3 &= 0 \\
a^3 + b^3 + c^3 + 3a^2b + 3ab^2 + 3a^2c + 3ac^2 + 3b^2c + 3bc^2 + 6abc &= 0 \\
a^3 + b^3 + c^3 + 3ab(a + b) + 3bc(b + c) + 3ca(c + a) + 6abc &= 0 \\
a^3 + b^3 + c^3 + 3abc + 3abc + 3abc + 6abc &= 0 \\
a^3 + b^3 + c^3 + 12abc &= 0 \\
a^3 + b^3 + c^3 &= -12abc.
\end{align*}
Now the established identity is given so the determinant can be written as
\[
\begin{vmatrix} a & b & c \\ b & c & a \\ c & a & b \end{vmatrix}
=
\begin{vmatrix} a & b & -1 - a - b \\ b & c & -1 - b - c \\ -1 - a - b & -1 - b - c & 1 \end{vmatrix}
\begin{vmatrix} a & b & -1 - a - b \\ b & c & -1 - b - c \\ -1 - a - b & -1 - b - c & 1 \end{vmatrix}
=
(-1 - a - b - 1 - b - c)(a^3 + b^3 + 12abc) = (-1 - 2b - c - a)^2.
\end{align*}
\end{align*}
Answers: $\boxed{(-1 - 2b - c - a)^2}$</answer>

